Preheat your oven to 220°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no
need to peel!). Pop on a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with
@olive oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then sprinkle over half the
@smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top
shelf of your oven for ~{30-35%minutes}, turning halfway.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).
Roughly chop the @vine tomatoes{2%medium}(roughly chopped into chunks).
Roughly chop the @black olives{30}(chopped).

Pop the @cod fillets{2} in a #bowl{} and drizzle with @olive oil{drizzle}. Season
with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} then sprinkle over the remaining
@smoked paprika{1/2%tsp}. Turn the fish to coat well in the marinade, then set
aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw fish.

Pop the vine tomatoes in a bowl and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp}, a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any).
Stir together then leave to one side - the tomatoes will release their juices
and create a lovely dressing. In a #small bowl{}, combine the olives with the
chopped parsley and @olive oil for the olives{1%tbsp}. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Take a moment to do any tidying up now. When the potatoes have about
~{10%minutes} left, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on
medium high heat. When hot add the cod and fry for ~{2-3%minutes} on each side,
turning carefully.

> IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the centre.

Serve the wedges on #plates{} with the fish and tomato salad alongside. Finish
by spooning the olive parsley salsa all over. Enjoy!